<div class="govuk-grid-row">
  <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
    

      <div id="contents" class="app-c-contents-list-with-body">
    
      
<div class="gem-c-govspeak govuk-govspeak direction-ltr" data-module="govspeak">
      <div class="govspeak">
<p>By using Union and Common Transit, you can move your goods quicker to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/eu-eea" class="govuk-link">EU countries</a> and <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/common-transit-convention-countries" class="govuk-link">Common Transit countries</a> because:</p>

<ul>
  <li>customs declarations and duties are not required at each border crossing</li>
  <li>you can complete some customs processes away from the border</li>
</ul>

<p>If you have not already, check if <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/check-if-you-can-use-transit-to-move-goods-to-the-eu-and-common-transit-countries" class="govuk-link">using Union or Common Transit is right for you</a>.</p>

<h2 id="if-you-want-someone-to-deal-with-customs-for-you">If you want someone to deal with customs for you</h2>

<p>If you want <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/appoint-someone-to-deal-with-customs-on-your-behalf" class="govuk-link">someone to deal with customs for you</a>, you must give written permission for them to do this first. This is known as getting a customs agent.</p>

<p>Depending on the agreement with your customs agent, you may need to do some customs processes yourself.</p>

<p>If you’re using a customs agent, check with them if you need to do anything else.</p>

<h2 id="if-youre-doing-customs-processes-yourself">If you’re doing customs processes yourself</h2>

<p>You’ll need:</p>

<ul>
  <li>
    <p>an Economic Operator Registration and Identification (EORI) number, you will need to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/eori" class="govuk-link">apply for an EORI</a> if you do not have one</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/import-and-export-customs-comprehensive-guarantees-ccgs" class="govuk-link">a guarantee</a> to cover your goods while they are being moved</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/using-the-new-computerised-transit-system-to-move-goods-across-the-eu-and-efta-countries#how-to-register-for-and-use-ncts-online" class="govuk-link">register for the New Computerised Transit System</a> to make transit declarations</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/export-declarations-and-the-national-export-system-export-procedures" class="govuk-link">register for the National Export System</a> if the transit movement is ending in a Common Transit country or goods are being exported outside the EU</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>choose which <a rel="external" href="https://ec.europa.eu/taxation_customs/dds2/col/col_home.jsp?Lang=en" class="govuk-link">UK office of departure</a> (a customs office) you want to start moving your goods from. This is where you present your goods with all documentation, ready to be sent.</p>
  </li>
</ul>

<p>You can choose to <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/apply-to-be-an-authorised-consignor-or-consignee" class="govuk-link">apply for authorised consignor status</a>. This will allow you to start transit at your own UK premises instead of at an office of departure.</p>

<h3 id="start-moving-your-goods">Start moving your goods</h3>

<p>Find out <a href="https://www.gov.uk/guidance/how-to-move-goods-between-or-through-common-transit-countries-including-the-eu" class="govuk-link">how to move goods using Union or Common Transit</a>.</p>
</div>
</div>


